cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a stochastic, derivative-free algorithm for numerical optimization, which is commonly used in evolutionary computing.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as optimization is a fundamental component of many machine learning algorithms.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as optimization is a key component of many AI applications.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses the time and memory complexity of the algorithm.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper proposes an optimization algorithm that can be applied to control systems.
